{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:titus.2",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "titus",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "Titus 2",
    "summary": "Source text for Titus 2 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:1",
      "text": "But as for you, teach what befits sound doctrine.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:2",
      "text": "Bid the older men be temperate, serious, sensible, sound in faith, in love, and in steadfastness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:3",
      "text": "Bid the older women likewise to be reverent in behavior, not to be slanderers or slaves to drink; they are to teach what is good,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:4",
      "text": "and so train the young women to love their husbands and children,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:5",
      "text": "to be sensible, chaste, domestic, kind, and submissive to their husbands, that the word of God may not be discredited.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:6",
      "text": "Likewise urge the younger men to control themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:7",
      "text": "Show yourself in all respects a model of good deeds, and in your teaching show integrity, gravity,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:8",
      "text": "and sound speech that cannot be censured, so that an opponent may be put to shame, having nothing evil to say of us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:9",
      "text": "Bid slaves to be submissive to their masters and to give satisfaction in every respect; they are not to be refractory,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:10",
      "text": "nor to pilfer, but to show entire and true fidelity, so that in everything they may adorn the doctrine of God our Savior.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:11",
      "text": "For the grace of God has appeared for the salvation of all men,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:12",
      "text": "training us to renounce irreligion and worldly passions, and to live sober, upright, and godly lives in this world,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:13",
      "text": "awaiting our blessed hope, the appearing of the glory of our great God and Savior Jesus Christ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:14",
      "text": "who gave himself for us to redeem us from all iniquity and to purify for himself a people of his own who are zealous for good deeds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:titus.2.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "titus",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Titus 2:15",
      "text": "Declare these things; exhort and reprove with all authority. Let no one disregard you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
